# Docs & examples registry

## Upkeep checklist (new or amended LD feature)

1. **Feature code** — `packages/model-viewer/src/features/` + mixin in `model-viewer.ts` (see `model-viewer-ld-features.mdc`)
2. **API reference** — add/update section in `packages/modelviewer.dev/data/docs.json`; link entries via `links` to example anchors
3. **Docs page slot** — new category: `<div id="{htmlName}-docs"></div>` in `packages/modelviewer.dev/docs/index.html`
4. **Example page** — `packages/modelviewer.dev/examples/ld_*/index.html`; call `init('examples-{htmlName}')`
5. **Examples registry** — `packages/modelviewer.dev/data/examples.json`
6. **Tests** — `packages/model-viewer/src/test/` + optional `packages/modelviewer.dev/test/` smoke tests
7. **Verify** — `cd packages/model-viewer && npm run build:dev`, `npm run serve`, browse docs + examples

## `examples.json` ordering

LD examples (`ld_*`) stay **below** upstream categories (Loading, Augmented Reality, Materials & Scene, Post Process Effects, etc.). Within the LD block, sort **alphabetically** by display `name`:

```
Materials & Scene
Post Process Effects
LD Ambient Occlusion
LD Bloom
LD Camera
…
```

## `docs.json` wiring

- `htmlName` must match `<div id="{htmlName}-docs">` in `docs/index.html`
- LD API sections alphabetically among LD entries (mirror examples)
- `init('docs')` on docs page; `init('examples-{htmlName}')` on example pages (`utils.ts`)
- API `links` → `../examples/ld_*/#{htmlId}` matching `htmlId` in `examples.json`

## Rebuild

After editing `packages/modelviewer.dev/src/docs-and-examples/`, run `npm run build --workspace=modelviewer.dev` to update `examples/built/docs-and-examples.js`.
